==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*fugla-'': cognate with Old Frisian [[fugel]] (Frisian [[fûgel]]), Old High German [[fogal]] (German [[Vogel]]), Old Saxon [[fugal]] (Dutch [[vogel]]), Old Norse [[fugl]] (Swedish [[fågel]], Danish [[fugl]]), Gothic [[𐍆𐌿𐌲𐌻𐍃]].  The Germanic base is a variant of ''*flugla-'' ‘fly’ (Old English [[fleogan|flēogan]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'fʊɣol/

===Noun===
'''fugol''' {{m}} (''pl'' '''fuglas''')

# a [[bird]]

